<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - GLOW PLUG CONTROL
        - FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>An open or shorted to ground glow plug relay or wait lamp circuit can be detected by an on demand output
            circuit check performed during the engine off tests.
        </para>
        <para>Glow plug and glow plug harness problems can not be detected by the ECM.</para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef12518100">3.107</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            and
            <emph type="bold">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="et1251817">3.22</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the circuit diagram and table for the Glow Plug Controller (GPC).
        </para>
        <figure id="ef12518100" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1133" filename="../figeg1/eg1133.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.107 - Glow Plug Control Circuit Diagram</caption>
        </figure>
        <table id="et1251817">
            <title>Table 3.22 - Glow Plug Controller (GPC)</title>
            <tgroup cols="4">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="72p"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="90p"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="90p"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="216p"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="4" spanname="S1T4"/>
                <spanspec namest="3" nameend="4" spanname="S3T4"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="2" spanname="S1T2"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="4" spanname="S1T4">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Glow Plug Relay Operation (Voltage Checks)</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S3T4">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>B+ terminal</para>
                            <para>to ground</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>B+</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S3T4">
                            <para>Relay switch power, B+ should be present at all times (terminal with single 6 gauge
                                wire). Check connection at starter or fusible links if no power (voltage) present.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Glow Plug</para>
                            <para>Feed to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>B+</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S3T4">
                            <para>Glow plug feed voltage should be present 10 to 120 sec. after key is cycled on,
                                dependent upon battery voltage, barometric pressure (altitude) and engine coolant
                                temperature.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>B to Ground</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>B+</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S3T4">
                            <para>Relay coil power. Voltage should be present when ign. key is ON - Check fuse if no
                                voltage.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Pin #58</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>0v/12v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S3T4">
                            <para>Glow plug control, switched to (grd) by ECM during operation. 0v = relay ON, 12v =
                                relay off.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="4" spanname="S1T4">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Glow Plug and Harness Operation</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="4" spanname="S1T4">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">(Measure glow plug resistance to ground with the pigtail connector
                                    installed at the valve cover connector:
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">then measure resistance from the glow plug feed stud to the harness
                                    connector.)
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S1T2">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S3T4">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Glow Plug</para>
                            <para>Number</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Pigtail Connector to Ground (B-)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Relay to Harness</para>
                            <para>Connector</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Comment</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Spec</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; .1 to 6 Ohm</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>&#60; 6 Ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" morerows="4">
                            <para>Relay to Harness Connector</para>
                            <note>
                                <para>All engine harness connectors for glow plug/injectors should be disconnected
                                    before taking measurements.
                                </para>
                                <para>High resistance could indicate an open circuit in the UVC (under the valve cover)
                                    harness or in the glow plug connector and the relay.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
